== Spanish ==
=== Etymology ===
Latin ''[[mente|mentē]]'', "mindedly" from ''[[mens]]'', "mind"
=== Suffix ===
'''-mente'''
# Used to form adverbs from adjectives, cf. English [[-ly]].
=== Usage note ===
Usually, the feminine form of the adjective is used, e.g. ''[[nuevamente]]'' (note use of ''[[nueva]]'' rather than ''[[nuevo]]''; ''*nuevomente'' would be incorrect)
